a Master Boot Record must be installed (eg. using \*(L"pwrite-device\*(R") on the
first sector of the whole disk.  The \s-1SYSLINUX\s0 package comes with some
suitable Master Boot Records.  See the \fIextlinux\fR\|(1) man page for further
information.
.PP
Additional configuration can be supplied to \s-1SYSLINUX\s0 by placing a file
called \f(CW\*(C`extlinux.conf\*(C'\fR on the filesystem under \f(CW\*(C`directory\*(C'\fR.  For further
information about the contents of this file, see \fIextlinux\fR\|(1).
